WEBVTT


00:00:31.605 --> 00:00:32.980
Is everything okay?

00:00:36.438 --> 00:00:37.438
Who are you?

00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:51.521
I'm Attorney Kujo.

00:00:52.438 --> 00:00:54.355
Please contact me if anything happens.

00:01:01.021 --> 00:01:03.813
Attorney… Kujo.

00:01:08.521 --> 00:01:11.646
Hey, hey, Shutan's looks
are simply awesome.

00:01:11.730 --> 00:01:13.730
He looks like an angel for real.

00:01:13.813 --> 00:01:15.521
Huh? It's Ayame.

00:01:15.605 --> 00:01:18.063
-Huh?
-Oh my gosh. He's so full of himself.

00:01:18.146 --> 00:01:20.063
Dang, you're right. So funny.

00:01:20.563 --> 00:01:23.230
Hey, smell this. I bought
the same perfume as my fave.

00:01:23.313 --> 00:01:25.563
Oh my gosh. That's so precious.

00:01:25.646 --> 00:01:30.230
I've bought too much merch.
I'm broke. I want to quit being a fan.

00:01:30.313 --> 00:01:32.521
-I know, right?
-Tsukiya is precious.

00:01:32.605 --> 00:01:34.938
MU:
SHIZUKU, I'M ALMOST DONE WITH WORK

00:01:35.021 --> 00:01:37.563
Oh my gosh.
My account was added to the list.

00:01:37.646 --> 00:01:39.688
I'm so jealous. That's too much editing.

00:01:39.771 --> 00:01:41.063
Shut up!

00:01:41.563 --> 00:01:42.813
I'm going home.

00:01:43.896 --> 00:01:45.605
Do you know her?

00:01:45.688 --> 00:01:48.688
Shizuku Kasagi.
She's a classmate from my hometown.

00:01:48.771 --> 00:01:50.188
She's annoying.

00:01:50.271 --> 00:01:53.063
She wraps her wrists in fake bandages.

00:01:53.146 --> 00:01:55.771
She's an attention seeker. It's gross.

00:02:01.313 --> 00:02:02.146
Mu?

00:02:02.230 --> 00:02:03.980
Sorry, Shizuku.

00:02:04.063 --> 00:02:05.396
I've got more work again.

00:02:06.105 --> 00:02:08.480
I'll be done when the first train leaves.

00:02:09.980 --> 00:02:11.313
I'm sorry.

00:02:13.521 --> 00:02:17.396
If you're bored, why not call a hot guy
from a dating app and have some fun?

00:02:19.438 --> 00:02:21.730
Where are the hot guys?

00:02:27.980 --> 00:02:28.938
Hey.

00:02:30.313 --> 00:02:31.605
That's a cute outfit.

00:02:32.230 --> 00:02:33.230
Huh?

00:02:33.896 --> 00:02:35.146
I'm Shuto.

00:02:35.230 --> 00:02:36.813
What's your name?

00:02:39.980 --> 00:02:41.396
Shizuku.

00:02:41.896 --> 00:02:43.813
Shizuku, huh?

00:02:44.313 --> 00:02:45.646
That's a nice name.

00:02:47.688 --> 00:02:50.438
It's dangerous to be alone at this hour.

00:02:51.938 --> 00:02:53.188
Wanna drink together?

00:02:55.105 --> 00:02:56.021
Yes.

00:02:57.896 --> 00:03:00.396
You didn't have to tag along.

00:03:00.480 --> 00:03:02.855
No, I'm worried about you, Attorney Kujo.

00:03:02.938 --> 00:03:04.271
Worried?

00:03:04.355 --> 00:03:06.355
Hey.

00:03:11.438 --> 00:03:13.938
Talking to him will only lead to trouble.

00:03:14.855 --> 00:03:17.063
No one knows what the future holds.

00:03:17.146 --> 00:03:20.230
No, I can see it clearly.
At least, when it comes to that man.

00:03:20.313 --> 00:03:24.980
If I end up causing you trouble,
Attorney Karasuma, I apologize in advance.

00:03:25.063 --> 00:03:27.688
If you're apologizing in advance,
why not stop here?

00:03:31.313 --> 00:03:33.521
Nothing beats this ice cream.

00:03:34.146 --> 00:03:35.855
Would you two like some?

00:03:35.938 --> 00:03:37.521
-Here.
-Oh…

00:03:38.146 --> 00:03:39.438
Thank you.

00:03:40.021 --> 00:03:40.855
Here you go.

00:03:40.938 --> 00:03:42.855
No, no, I'll pass.

00:03:43.355 --> 00:03:45.146
You don't like ice cream?

00:03:45.230 --> 00:03:46.188
No, it's not that.

00:03:46.271 --> 00:03:47.105
Oh…

00:03:48.230 --> 00:03:51.021
You don't want to accept anything
from a yakuza, huh?

00:03:51.105 --> 00:03:52.480
That's a waste.

00:03:52.980 --> 00:03:54.813
The ice cream is going to melt.

00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:59.146
So, Mr. Kyogoku,
what did you want to talk about?

00:03:59.813 --> 00:04:00.730
Huh?

00:04:01.855 --> 00:04:05.813
Oh, there's a chairman
who I'm looking out for.

00:04:06.313 --> 00:04:10.396
The AV studio he's the chairman of
is being sued, and he's in trouble.

00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:12.021
An adult video studio?

00:04:13.605 --> 00:04:15.771
What are they being sued for?

00:04:15.855 --> 00:04:19.813
A former actress claims to have been
forced to appear in an adult video,

00:04:20.313 --> 00:04:24.313
so she's demanding a ban
on the sale of her past works

00:04:24.396 --> 00:04:25.980
and is seeking damages.

00:04:26.063 --> 00:04:31.146
A human rights attorney,
named Reiko Kameoka, is uncompromising,

00:04:31.230 --> 00:04:32.688
and the company's in trouble.

00:04:32.771 --> 00:04:34.355
Reiko Kameoka?

00:04:37.396 --> 00:04:40.521
The laws in this country
are too lenient on sex crimes.

00:04:40.605 --> 00:04:43.146
The perpetrators escape punishment

00:04:43.230 --> 00:04:45.105
and repeatedly commit sexual violence

00:04:45.188 --> 00:04:46.480
without a shred of guilt.

00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:50.480
Sexual violence is murder of the soul.

00:04:50.980 --> 00:04:53.771
The AV industry promotes sexual violence,

00:04:53.855 --> 00:04:55.521
and it's the embodiment of evil.

00:04:56.605 --> 00:04:57.938
Do you know her?

00:04:58.438 --> 00:05:01.688
Yes. Attorney Kameoka was my classmate.

00:05:02.188 --> 00:05:04.396
Huh? Really?

00:05:05.271 --> 00:05:07.271
They are forced to work.

00:05:07.355 --> 00:05:09.438
Their private parts are exposed forever,

00:05:09.521 --> 00:05:10.563
humiliating them.

00:05:10.646 --> 00:05:11.855
We must protect

00:05:11.938 --> 00:05:13.813
the human rights of AV actresses,

00:05:13.896 --> 00:05:15.896
who are victims and socially vulnerable.

00:05:15.980 --> 00:05:18.396
We must eliminate
the structure of exploitation.

00:05:19.730 --> 00:05:21.605
We must save the weak.

00:05:23.396 --> 00:05:24.896
Stop sexual violence!

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:27.396
No AV industry!

00:05:27.896 --> 00:05:29.521
Stop sexual violence!

00:05:29.605 --> 00:05:34.271
It makes me sick when human rights lawyers
say they want to save the weak.

00:05:35.146 --> 00:05:38.355
They feel good about themselves
by proclaiming ideals.

00:05:40.105 --> 00:05:42.813
Weak people who live
by cutting corners don't fight.

00:05:42.896 --> 00:05:45.355
They just complain, grumble, and backstab.

00:05:45.438 --> 00:05:47.646
You weaken an army
by caring for the injured.

00:05:47.730 --> 00:05:50.146
It's better to kill them
and cut your losses.

00:05:50.938 --> 00:05:52.980
Or, in a world of competition,

00:05:53.063 --> 00:05:54.688
you'll end up prey to predators.

00:05:56.480 --> 00:05:57.563
Anyway,

00:05:58.646 --> 00:06:00.771
if they want to rant about human rights,

00:06:00.855 --> 00:06:04.730
I want them to protect
the human rights of us yakuza too.

00:06:04.813 --> 00:06:06.563
Do yakuza need human rights?

00:06:06.646 --> 00:06:07.646
Attorney Karasuma.

00:06:07.730 --> 00:06:10.146
Because yakuza are overwhelmingly strong.

00:06:10.230 --> 00:06:11.813
That's prejudiced thinking.

00:06:11.896 --> 00:06:15.021
We can't stay at hotels.
We can't open bank accounts.

00:06:15.105 --> 00:06:16.730
We can't buy life insurance.

00:06:16.813 --> 00:06:17.813
You deserve it.

00:06:17.896 --> 00:06:19.896
-Hey, you!
-Stop.

00:06:19.980 --> 00:06:23.438
That attorney is still young,
unlike Attorney Kujo.

00:06:23.521 --> 00:06:25.646
Eat some ice cream and cool your head.

00:06:25.730 --> 00:06:26.730
Thank you very much.

00:06:26.813 --> 00:06:30.771
Well, Attorney Kujo, I'm counting on you.

00:06:38.230 --> 00:06:39.813
Are you going to take the case?

00:06:40.438 --> 00:06:41.438
Yes.

00:06:42.313 --> 00:06:43.896
It's my job.

00:07:17.730 --> 00:07:20.855
Thank you very much, Attorney Kameoka.

00:07:20.938 --> 00:07:24.813
At first, I wasn't sure
about female attorneys,

00:07:24.896 --> 00:07:27.896
but the phrase "tough as any man"
could've been made for you.

00:07:27.980 --> 00:07:30.188
Do you know the term "tough as any man"

00:07:30.271 --> 00:07:35.021
comes from the discriminatory idea
that women are inferior to men?

00:07:35.105 --> 00:07:36.980
Oh, well…

00:07:37.688 --> 00:07:41.813
You're a strong attorney
despite being a beautiful woman.

00:07:41.896 --> 00:07:43.355
I was complimenting you.

00:07:43.438 --> 00:07:46.855
Appearance and gender have nothing to do
with an attorney's ability.

00:07:46.938 --> 00:07:51.396
I just do everything I can for my clients.

00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:54.105
Mr. Suzuki, you take the subway, right?

00:07:54.605 --> 00:07:55.438
Yes.

00:07:55.938 --> 00:07:57.063
You can go ahead.

00:08:00.896 --> 00:08:02.271
W-Well, then,

00:08:03.021 --> 00:08:04.521
thank you very much.

00:08:07.188 --> 00:08:08.730
Ms. Kameoka.

00:08:08.813 --> 00:08:10.521
Attorney Nagaragi.

00:08:11.396 --> 00:08:13.646
You've been doing very well lately.

00:08:13.730 --> 00:08:15.521
No, no. What is it?

00:08:15.605 --> 00:08:17.813
Oh, I just wanted to have a little chat.

00:08:21.563 --> 00:08:22.938
You're single, right?

00:08:23.438 --> 00:08:24.938
Don't you want to get married?

00:08:25.438 --> 00:08:29.396
Why are you asking this all of a sudden?
This is harassment, Attorney Nagaragi.

00:08:31.480 --> 00:08:33.938
-Are you saying this deliberately?
-Yes.

00:08:34.938 --> 00:08:39.188
I saw your lecture on married couples
having different surnames in a video,

00:08:39.813 --> 00:08:41.771
and I have the perfect partner for you.

00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:44.146
It's none of your business, but who is it?

00:08:45.355 --> 00:08:46.355
Attorney Kujo.

00:08:47.063 --> 00:08:48.355
Attorney Kujo?

00:08:49.480 --> 00:08:51.355
Are you talking about Mr. Kurama?

00:08:52.146 --> 00:08:54.271
Please stop joking. He's such a weirdo.

00:08:55.271 --> 00:08:58.605
He defends antisocial forces.
I've only heard bad rumors about him.

00:09:01.146 --> 00:09:05.355
Do you think I'm a good match for someone
who's involved with antisocial forces?

00:09:05.438 --> 00:09:06.688
Yes.

00:09:07.855 --> 00:09:10.438
I can picture the two of you
standing side by side.

00:09:10.938 --> 00:09:12.021
I'm offended.

00:09:12.105 --> 00:09:13.896
He's a man of principle.

00:09:13.980 --> 00:09:15.480
This is ridiculous.

00:09:15.980 --> 00:09:17.438
I'm going home.

00:09:18.021 --> 00:09:19.355
Meet him once

00:09:20.105 --> 00:09:22.396
and rekindle an old friendship.

00:09:24.021 --> 00:09:25.438
Excuse me.

00:09:40.521 --> 00:09:44.105
Ms. Kasagi, how many times
do I have to tell you?

00:09:44.188 --> 00:09:46.688
The price tags and products
are all over the place.

00:09:48.396 --> 00:09:49.980
I'm sorry.

00:09:52.938 --> 00:09:55.938
No matter what I do,
I'm inferior to regular people.

00:10:03.063 --> 00:10:04.521
Shuto?

00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:06.521
Are you feeling down?

00:10:07.396 --> 00:10:08.480
Come to the bar.

00:10:08.563 --> 00:10:10.313
I'll comfort you.

00:10:11.521 --> 00:10:15.521
I want you to comfort me, Shuto…

00:10:17.855 --> 00:10:20.021
But I'm out of savings.

00:10:20.105 --> 00:10:22.230
The queen of being broke.

00:10:22.313 --> 00:10:24.396
I can't go to the bar.

00:10:25.146 --> 00:10:25.980
Sob.

00:10:33.521 --> 00:10:35.938
You can pay later. Just come.

00:10:36.980 --> 00:10:38.563
I want to see you, Shizuku.

00:10:49.813 --> 00:10:52.438
Ah, today is fun too.

00:10:52.521 --> 00:10:54.688
Thank you for coming
all the time, Shizuku.

00:10:54.771 --> 00:10:57.896
-Shuto, you're so good-looking.
-Hmm?

00:10:57.980 --> 00:10:59.813
At first, I thought you were a host.

00:10:59.896 --> 00:11:02.063
I told you I'm not a host.

00:11:02.563 --> 00:11:05.688
I'm an actor… working part-time here.

00:11:06.813 --> 00:11:09.146
I see. You're an actor.

00:11:09.230 --> 00:11:10.438
What shows were you in?

00:11:10.521 --> 00:11:13.896
Oh, I almost got a role
in a superhero show.

00:11:14.771 --> 00:11:18.188
I'm sure you'll be a great actor, Shuto.

00:11:19.355 --> 00:11:20.813
I've still got a ways to go.

00:11:21.771 --> 00:11:23.646
What's your dream, Shizuku?

00:11:25.396 --> 00:11:26.896
My dream?

00:11:28.271 --> 00:11:30.646
I'm just trying to survive.

00:11:31.230 --> 00:11:34.730
If I had to say, I wanna leave home.
I wanna leave right now.

00:11:34.813 --> 00:11:37.105
I'm working part-time so I can move out.

00:11:37.938 --> 00:11:39.313
Problems with your parents?

00:11:40.605 --> 00:11:42.563
It's not my parents…

00:11:43.563 --> 00:11:47.313
I really hate
my mom's boyfriend, Tonohata.

00:11:47.855 --> 00:11:49.896
-Tono?
-What?

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:51.896
Eat whatever you want with this.

00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.021
Uh-huh.

00:11:53.563 --> 00:11:55.938
Shizuku, I'm going to work.

00:11:56.438 --> 00:11:57.855
See you.

00:12:00.980 --> 00:12:05.105
He does nasty things to me
when my mom's not around.

00:12:07.480 --> 00:12:10.521
He hits me if I resist,
so I'm really scared.

00:12:12.813 --> 00:12:13.688
Oh.

00:12:14.813 --> 00:12:18.271
I start blabbering when I'm drunk.

00:12:18.355 --> 00:12:21.105
Oh no, please don't hate me.

00:12:21.855 --> 00:12:24.355
There's no way I'd hate you
for such a thing.

00:12:26.105 --> 00:12:28.146
You come to see me every day.

00:12:28.896 --> 00:12:31.021
You spend a lot of money.

00:12:31.813 --> 00:12:32.855
I'm only grateful.

00:12:33.980 --> 00:12:35.396
I'm so happy.

00:12:37.188 --> 00:12:41.188
But I'm going to run out of money.

00:12:42.563 --> 00:12:45.188
My tab is almost maxed out.

00:12:47.063 --> 00:12:47.896
Shizuku.

00:12:49.646 --> 00:12:53.771
Can we be alone after the bar closes?

00:13:03.230 --> 00:13:07.480
I feel so safe when I'm with you, Shuto.

00:13:10.438 --> 00:13:13.188
I've never felt this safe before.

00:13:14.688 --> 00:13:15.813
Is that so?

00:13:16.646 --> 00:13:18.063
I'm glad.

00:13:19.855 --> 00:13:20.980
Yeah.

00:13:23.230 --> 00:13:25.646
I have a job I want to introduce you to.

00:13:29.438 --> 00:13:31.396
Oh, okay, okay.

00:13:32.063 --> 00:13:34.396
It's sex work, isn't it?

00:13:41.105 --> 00:13:45.855
I'll do anything
to keep seeing you, Shuto.

00:13:47.646 --> 00:13:52.063
The other girls I know are working as
call girls for their host boyfriends too.

00:13:52.563 --> 00:13:53.646
That's not it.

00:13:55.021 --> 00:13:57.105
Shizuku, don't underestimate yourself.

00:13:58.605 --> 00:13:59.438
Huh?

00:14:01.855 --> 00:14:03.605
And action!

00:14:04.230 --> 00:14:05.188
Okay.

00:14:07.188 --> 00:14:11.355
The scout, Shuto, referred me.
I'm Shizuku Kasagi.

00:14:11.438 --> 00:14:14.855
Your acquaintances
will definitely find out.

00:14:14.938 --> 00:14:16.896
-Are you okay with that?
-Yes.

00:14:16.980 --> 00:14:18.230
I'm okay with it.

00:14:18.313 --> 00:14:21.313
I'm not worried about anyone
finding out about this.

00:14:22.146 --> 00:14:23.230
But

00:14:24.146 --> 00:14:27.230
can someone like me become one?

00:14:27.313 --> 00:14:30.313
Ms. Kasagi, you underestimate yourself.

00:14:31.271 --> 00:14:34.230
You have the talent
to become a top-tier actress.

00:14:34.313 --> 00:14:35.980
A top-tier actress?

00:14:36.063 --> 00:14:40.063
Only a handful of elite actresses
are considered top-tier actresses.

00:14:40.646 --> 00:14:42.521
Have confidence in yourself.

00:14:42.605 --> 00:14:43.563
Okay.

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:47.396
The one thing I don't have is confidence.

00:14:47.480 --> 00:14:48.646
It's okay.

00:14:49.313 --> 00:14:52.313
Your success
will eventually lead to confidence.

00:14:53.105 --> 00:14:54.438
You are

00:14:54.938 --> 00:14:56.855
a diamond in the rough.

00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:17.521
You're so pretty, Shizuku.

00:15:17.605 --> 00:15:20.271
They'll film you beautifully.
Everything will be okay.

00:15:20.355 --> 00:15:23.855
Ms. Tashiro, I'm so, so grateful.

00:15:23.938 --> 00:15:24.938
Uh-huh.

00:15:27.105 --> 00:15:28.021
But…

00:15:30.021 --> 00:15:31.230
I'm scared.

00:15:32.521 --> 00:15:34.480
It'll be fine.

00:15:34.563 --> 00:15:37.480
I'll be watching over you the whole time,

00:15:37.563 --> 00:15:38.855
so don't worry.

00:15:39.605 --> 00:15:41.313
Thank you so much.

00:15:45.646 --> 00:15:46.688
You're all done.

00:16:05.563 --> 00:16:06.605
Shizuku!

00:16:07.105 --> 00:16:08.688
Good luck with the shoot!

00:16:09.438 --> 00:16:11.480
I'll always be with you in spirit!

00:16:31.313 --> 00:16:33.396
Thank you for letting me be here today.

00:16:34.438 --> 00:16:35.688
Nice to meet you.

00:16:35.771 --> 00:16:39.105
Mr. Kyogoku referred me to you.
I'm Mr. Koyama from Komuora Kikaku.

00:16:39.855 --> 00:16:42.146
I'm Attorney Kujo.

00:16:42.688 --> 00:16:45.771
-Attorney Karasuma.
-I'm here about the Momoka Shiraishi case.

00:16:45.855 --> 00:16:49.855
She's suing us to recall her adult films,
claiming she was forced to act in them.

00:16:51.146 --> 00:16:54.855
To be honest,
this case is a losing battle.

00:16:54.938 --> 00:16:55.855
Losing?

00:16:55.938 --> 00:16:57.646
-Yes.
-Why is that?

00:16:57.730 --> 00:17:00.396
I know this was before
the new AV law was enacted,

00:17:00.480 --> 00:17:01.938
but based on past precedents,

00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:05.313
Ms. Shiraishi's appearances
in the adult videos

00:17:05.396 --> 00:17:09.230
will likely be judged
a quasi-employment contract.

00:17:09.313 --> 00:17:14.021
In this case, the Civil Code's provisions
on employment and labor apply,

00:17:14.105 --> 00:17:17.063
so even mid-contract,
she can't be stopped from quitting.

00:17:17.146 --> 00:17:19.813
With her demands
to remove past work and seek damages,

00:17:19.896 --> 00:17:23.730
we must present objective evidence
that she was not forced into appearing.

00:17:23.813 --> 00:17:26.855
Otherwise, our chances of winning
are virtually zero.

00:17:26.938 --> 00:17:30.730
We'll stop the other side's attorney
from using the media to blow this up.

00:17:30.813 --> 00:17:32.646
What a pain.

00:17:32.730 --> 00:17:34.521
Since the new AV law was enacted,

00:17:34.605 --> 00:17:37.146
our industry has been clean,
unlike the old days.

00:17:37.646 --> 00:17:41.313
Now, we are thorough in signing contracts
with actresses before filming.

00:17:41.396 --> 00:17:43.730
So you didn't sign contracts in the past?

00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:44.813
Huh?

00:17:49.105 --> 00:17:51.230
Oh, w-well…

00:17:52.605 --> 00:17:54.605
Momoka Shiraishi, who filed the lawsuit,

00:17:54.688 --> 00:17:57.271
is an actress
who's been active since that time.

00:18:00.646 --> 00:18:03.355
She has appeared in more than 300 videos.

00:18:03.438 --> 00:18:06.688
And now she suddenly claims
that she was forced to appear in them.

00:18:07.230 --> 00:18:09.480
Since she's appeared
in more than 300 videos,

00:18:09.563 --> 00:18:12.563
it may indicate that she was
not forced to appear in them.

00:18:13.105 --> 00:18:16.146
By the way,
do you have any idea as to why?

00:18:16.646 --> 00:18:18.355
It's a man. A man.

00:18:19.271 --> 00:18:22.313
Ms. Shiraishi had a boyfriend
who was violent.

00:18:22.396 --> 00:18:26.105
At first, she endured being beaten
and having her hard-earned money taken.

00:18:26.855 --> 00:18:30.188
But she couldn't take
the violence anymore,

00:18:30.688 --> 00:18:34.438
and she fled to Reiko Kameoka,
a human rights attorney.

00:18:35.021 --> 00:18:38.521
For some reason, she turned her anger
on us instead of the violent guy.

00:18:38.605 --> 00:18:41.521
How was your company's relationship
with Momoka Shiraishi?

00:18:41.605 --> 00:18:42.938
It was good.

00:18:43.021 --> 00:18:45.771
She even sent me a postcard
from her overseas trip.

00:18:48.646 --> 00:18:49.605
This.

00:18:52.396 --> 00:18:53.230
I'LL DO MY BEST!

00:18:53.313 --> 00:18:54.855
It's ridiculous.

00:18:54.938 --> 00:18:57.563
They only impose their claims.

00:18:57.646 --> 00:19:02.063
What kind of human rights lawyer is she?
She should consider our human rights too.

00:19:02.730 --> 00:19:05.813
Anyway, I'm counting on you, sir.

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:08.813
I'll take the case,

00:19:08.896 --> 00:19:13.521
but whether she continues with AV or not
is up to Ms. Shiraishi to decide.

00:19:30.271 --> 00:19:32.105
You're regretting it, aren't you?

00:19:33.146 --> 00:19:33.980
Regretting what?

00:19:35.355 --> 00:19:38.105
Taking on such a case.

00:19:38.855 --> 00:19:41.396
You should stay away from Mr. Kyogoku.

00:19:41.480 --> 00:19:44.730
No, I was thinking about something else.

00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:46.980
What were you thinking about?

00:19:47.855 --> 00:19:50.730
Are there any attorneys
who aren't human rights attorneys?

00:19:50.813 --> 00:19:51.688
Huh?

00:19:52.188 --> 00:19:55.188
Attorneys receive requests
from someone and do their work.

00:19:55.271 --> 00:19:59.146
They fight in court,
respecting that person's human rights.

00:20:00.063 --> 00:20:02.563
Doesn't that make you, me,
and all attorneys

00:20:02.646 --> 00:20:04.063
human rights attorneys?

00:20:04.146 --> 00:20:07.521
Well, you see, a human rights attorney is…

00:20:08.813 --> 00:20:10.813
It's Attorney Kameoka.

00:20:10.896 --> 00:20:12.146
Hello?

00:20:12.646 --> 00:20:14.646
It's been a while. It's Ms. Kameoka.

00:20:15.146 --> 00:20:16.771
Mr. Kurama… That's not it.

00:20:16.855 --> 00:20:17.938
It's Kujo now, right?

00:20:18.855 --> 00:20:20.021
Your last name changed,

00:20:20.105 --> 00:20:23.605
but your number is still the same
as when you were a student.

00:20:24.230 --> 00:20:26.563
It's been a while, Attorney Kameoka.

00:20:28.563 --> 00:20:32.271
Attorney Kujo, you're representing
Komuora Kikaku, right?

00:20:32.771 --> 00:20:34.730
May I ask one thing before we face off?

00:20:36.146 --> 00:20:37.271
Sure.

00:20:37.355 --> 00:20:39.230
You have a daughter, right?

00:20:40.188 --> 00:20:43.605
What would you do
if your daughter was forced to do AV?

00:20:44.105 --> 00:20:47.396
Attorney Kameoka, about this case,

00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:51.688
is it possible that an AV actress who's
been in over 300 films was forced into it?

00:20:51.771 --> 00:20:54.188
Don't evade my question with a question.

00:20:54.271 --> 00:20:56.396
This isn't a problem with the AV industry.

00:20:56.480 --> 00:21:00.146
Isn't she just shifting the blame
to escape from domestic violence?

00:21:00.730 --> 00:21:03.646
Just answer my question.

00:21:03.730 --> 00:21:07.438
What would you do
if your daughter was forced to do AV?

00:21:07.521 --> 00:21:08.938
That's a huge leap.

00:21:09.438 --> 00:21:10.896
It's irrelevant to this case.

00:21:14.855 --> 00:21:16.563
Then I'll change my question.

00:21:18.355 --> 00:21:20.855
Why are you defending antisocial forces?

00:21:22.521 --> 00:21:25.771
I get it if it's for social justice
to prevent false accusations.

00:21:25.855 --> 00:21:29.771
But what you're doing
is encouraging crime.

00:21:32.188 --> 00:21:36.105
I don't think it's wise for an attorney
to make a judgment on justice.

00:21:36.188 --> 00:21:39.605
You're a human being
before you're an attorney, right?

00:21:40.105 --> 00:21:42.605
If you can't even make a judgment
on good and evil,

00:21:42.688 --> 00:21:43.813
you're not a human.

00:21:48.646 --> 00:21:53.438
If you serve an evil person in power,
you'll eventually be swallowed up.

00:22:03.313 --> 00:22:06.438
Isn't she what you call
a human rights attorney?

00:22:06.521 --> 00:22:08.355
Is that so?

00:22:09.146 --> 00:22:12.146
To me, she's not an attorney,

00:22:12.230 --> 00:22:16.105
but a thinker or activist
with a strong desire for approval.

00:22:16.188 --> 00:22:20.063
Well, at the very least,
I don't think she's a crooked lawyer.

00:22:20.563 --> 00:22:23.646
I think you would get along with her.

00:22:23.730 --> 00:22:27.021
I'm afraid she'd corner me
the moment we meet.

00:22:27.105 --> 00:22:30.021
But I agree with her last words.

00:22:30.688 --> 00:22:32.021
Attorney Kujo.

00:22:33.521 --> 00:22:35.938
I advise you to be cautious

00:22:36.563 --> 00:22:39.480
about requests from Mr. Kyogoku.

00:22:44.646 --> 00:22:46.105
I'll keep that in mind.

00:22:50.271 --> 00:22:51.105
NO. 1 ROOKIE

00:22:51.188 --> 00:22:54.271
Jackpot! It's a huge hit!

00:22:54.355 --> 00:22:56.355
We did spend a lot on advertising,

00:22:56.438 --> 00:22:59.355
but it's selling like crazy, Shizuku.

00:22:59.938 --> 00:23:03.396
Thank you, Mr. Ao!
I'll do my best at the shoot tomorrow.

00:23:03.480 --> 00:23:04.313
All right!

00:23:04.396 --> 00:23:06.521
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:23:10.146 --> 00:23:11.730
It's delicious.

00:23:11.813 --> 00:23:15.146
-Are you sure? It's expensive.
-Yeah. It's to celebrate your debut.

00:23:15.230 --> 00:23:17.021
And you got first place, right?

00:23:17.105 --> 00:23:18.146
That's amazing!

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:22.355
Oh, I got paid,
so I can pay you back for the tab.

00:23:22.438 --> 00:23:26.063
It's okay. You're gonna sell even more,
so you can pay me back later.

00:23:27.063 --> 00:23:27.980
Okay.

00:23:28.646 --> 00:23:32.521
More importantly, the actor who got
the morning drama role wants to meet you.

00:23:32.605 --> 00:23:35.980
No, as long as I have you,
I don't need anyone else.

00:23:37.688 --> 00:23:38.730
I see.

00:23:38.813 --> 00:23:39.730
Yeah.

00:23:41.771 --> 00:23:44.438
Ah, I'm so happy.

00:23:45.355 --> 00:23:46.563
Hey, Shizuku.

00:23:47.105 --> 00:23:49.396
Can you wait until the bar closes today?

00:23:49.480 --> 00:23:50.313
Yeah.

00:23:50.896 --> 00:23:53.980
-I'll hold you until morning.
-Yay!

00:23:57.813 --> 00:23:58.646
Oh!

00:23:59.271 --> 00:24:01.771
MOM:
SHIZUKU, THE MONEY'S DUE TODAY

00:24:01.855 --> 00:24:03.438
COME HOME

00:24:03.521 --> 00:24:05.313
WHERE ARE YOU?

00:24:07.855 --> 00:24:08.688
What's wrong?

00:24:09.480 --> 00:24:10.771
Sorry.

00:24:12.146 --> 00:24:14.188
Mom's mad.

00:24:15.813 --> 00:24:17.813
What you're saying is so damn annoying.

00:24:17.896 --> 00:24:20.688
Ow, ow! That hurts, Tono.
It hurts. It hurts!

00:24:20.771 --> 00:24:24.813
I told you, you need
to use your brain to make money!

00:24:24.896 --> 00:24:26.188
Look at this.

00:24:28.063 --> 00:24:30.563
A super fake Polex. It's a grade N.

00:24:31.063 --> 00:24:32.230
I got it from Korea.

00:24:33.646 --> 00:24:37.105
I took this to a few pawn shops
and sold it for 500,000.

00:24:37.188 --> 00:24:38.021
Seriously?

00:24:38.105 --> 00:24:39.980
Huh? They didn't find out, Tono?

00:24:40.063 --> 00:24:42.605
I was like, "Who knows?
Maybe you switched it out."

00:24:42.688 --> 00:24:44.146
And I forced them to buy it.

00:24:46.688 --> 00:24:49.438
Hey, I'll sell it to you
for a special deal of 250,000.

00:24:50.105 --> 00:24:52.230
You could sell it in an online auction.

00:24:52.313 --> 00:24:54.188
Nah, I don't have that kind of money.

00:24:54.688 --> 00:24:57.646
Hey, you said you'd pay me back
the 100,000 today, right?

00:25:00.813 --> 00:25:02.146
Can I try something?

00:25:08.813 --> 00:25:11.605
You're such a pain, you broke dumbass!

00:25:11.688 --> 00:25:15.521
-If you sell it for 500,000--
-Hey, don't break the glasses.

00:25:15.605 --> 00:25:19.646
You got a problem with that? Or not?
Huh? I can't hear you! Which is it?

00:25:19.730 --> 00:25:20.938
Oh, Shizuku.

00:25:21.646 --> 00:25:23.313
Oh, Shizuku.

00:25:23.396 --> 00:25:26.563
Where have you been wandering around?
I was worried about you.

00:25:26.646 --> 00:25:28.188
I was just working.

00:25:29.896 --> 00:25:32.313
You look kinda grown-up.
Did you get a boyfriend?

00:25:32.396 --> 00:25:33.313
Nope.

00:25:33.813 --> 00:25:34.646
Mom.

00:25:36.480 --> 00:25:37.396
Yeah?

00:25:38.771 --> 00:25:40.355
Here's the money.

00:25:40.438 --> 00:25:41.355
Oh.

00:25:43.188 --> 00:25:44.230
What?

00:25:44.730 --> 00:25:47.355
This much? What?
Where did you get this money?

00:25:47.438 --> 00:25:48.605
From my part-time job.

00:25:48.688 --> 00:25:50.230
Wow.

00:25:50.980 --> 00:25:53.813
Well, I'm going out.

00:25:53.896 --> 00:25:54.980
Oh.

00:26:01.896 --> 00:26:02.771
Hey.

00:26:03.355 --> 00:26:04.605
Give me that money.

00:26:04.688 --> 00:26:05.896
No way!

00:26:05.980 --> 00:26:08.355
How much do you think
you've run up on your tab?

00:26:08.438 --> 00:26:10.355
I'm the one the boss will yell at!

00:26:10.438 --> 00:26:12.271
Shut up. You cover it for me!

00:26:12.355 --> 00:26:15.188
Tono, you need to get a job already.

00:26:18.188 --> 00:26:20.480
Don't act all high and mighty!

00:26:20.563 --> 00:26:23.938
Thank you for finding me a good girl.

00:26:24.021 --> 00:26:28.521
Well, I didn't expect Shizuku
to sell that much.

00:26:28.605 --> 00:26:30.771
She still has a lot of potential.

00:26:32.396 --> 00:26:35.146
An AV actress can't last long
if she's not strong.

00:26:35.646 --> 00:26:37.521
If she's weak, she won't make it.

00:26:38.063 --> 00:26:41.105
She needs to be tough
and not worry about the little things.

00:26:41.938 --> 00:26:45.480
As for mentally unstable girls,
we have to continue tricking them.

00:26:45.563 --> 00:26:50.813
If Shizuku is the latter,
I'll leave her emotional care to you.

00:26:51.438 --> 00:26:53.230
Leave it to me.

00:26:54.230 --> 00:26:55.230
Oh,

00:26:55.313 --> 00:26:57.105
another girl's about to go broke,

00:26:57.188 --> 00:26:59.438
so I think I can introduce her to you.

00:26:59.521 --> 00:27:01.480
You're a hard worker.

00:27:01.563 --> 00:27:03.896
Well, if the girl I introduce makes money,

00:27:03.980 --> 00:27:06.896
I get 10% permanently
as the talent scout, after all.

00:27:07.688 --> 00:27:09.313
It's a good business.

00:27:10.355 --> 00:27:12.396
I'm sorry. I'll call you back.

00:27:13.480 --> 00:27:14.480
Shizuku?

00:27:16.021 --> 00:27:16.855
What's wrong?

00:27:16.938 --> 00:27:18.563
I hate this.

00:27:19.605 --> 00:27:21.188
I don't want to go home.

00:27:22.563 --> 00:27:25.105
I want to be beside you forever.

00:27:32.146 --> 00:27:33.063
Yeah.

00:27:34.896 --> 00:27:35.855
Huh?

00:27:36.355 --> 00:27:37.730
Postpone the interview?

00:27:37.813 --> 00:27:38.646
Right.

00:27:38.730 --> 00:27:42.480
Momoka Shiraishi agreed to settle
with the other party at this stage.

00:27:43.938 --> 00:27:47.605
So what about the big scoop
that was going to expose the AV industry?

00:27:48.396 --> 00:27:49.896
It's not happening.

00:27:50.480 --> 00:27:51.813
They got us.

00:27:52.396 --> 00:27:55.646
The opposing attorney put her up to it,
and she backed out.

00:27:56.313 --> 00:27:57.521
Attorney Kujo,

00:27:57.605 --> 00:28:01.313
thank you for settling
the Shiraishi case out of court.

00:28:01.396 --> 00:28:02.396
No problem.

00:28:04.480 --> 00:28:05.771
It was just as you said.

00:28:05.855 --> 00:28:08.355
Her lawyer was trying
to prop up Momoka Shiraishi

00:28:08.438 --> 00:28:10.896
and push her into the media, face and all.

00:28:11.938 --> 00:28:14.230
I just provided a clear explanation.

00:28:15.355 --> 00:28:17.438
It seems to have worked quite well.

00:28:17.938 --> 00:28:20.813
Why did Momoka Shiraishi sue
in the first place?

00:28:20.896 --> 00:28:22.230
Oh,

00:28:22.730 --> 00:28:25.313
her abusive boyfriend hit her,
and she was confused.

00:28:25.396 --> 00:28:29.146
Ms. Kameoka riled her up, so she couldn't
back down. She later regretted it.

00:28:29.230 --> 00:28:31.438
What's going to happen to her now?

00:28:31.521 --> 00:28:36.188
Well, she can't come back to this industry
after turning against us.

00:28:36.271 --> 00:28:38.771
Had she not quit like this,
she could've come back.

00:28:42.396 --> 00:28:45.355
All the girls who make it big
always come back again.

00:28:45.438 --> 00:28:47.521
They can't do any other decent job.

00:28:48.646 --> 00:28:50.980
And, well, I guess
they remember the good times

00:28:51.063 --> 00:28:53.480
when they had somewhere they belonged.

00:28:57.438 --> 00:28:59.105
-Your sweet and sour pork.
-Oh.

00:28:59.188 --> 00:29:00.938
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

00:29:01.438 --> 00:29:04.480
It's rare for you to ask us out.

00:29:04.563 --> 00:29:06.146
You even invited Attorney Kujo.

00:29:06.896 --> 00:29:11.021
I have to regularly warn
you crooked lawyers.

00:29:11.105 --> 00:29:12.230
Crooked lawyers?

00:29:12.313 --> 00:29:15.563
It's like fire safety,
like crime prevention.

00:29:15.646 --> 00:29:17.771
Sorry for always making you
worry about us.

00:29:18.480 --> 00:29:19.438
Now,

00:29:20.105 --> 00:29:21.271
I need some advice.

00:29:21.355 --> 00:29:23.355
The consultation fee is 5,000 yen.

00:29:23.438 --> 00:29:24.813
Not a legal consultation.

00:29:24.896 --> 00:29:25.896
Oh…

00:29:27.480 --> 00:29:28.313
Here.

00:29:32.313 --> 00:29:33.730
A dating app?

00:29:33.813 --> 00:29:37.021
I made an account,
but I'm not getting any messages. Why?

00:29:37.105 --> 00:29:40.146
Well, you wrote a lot of conditions.

00:29:40.688 --> 00:29:42.521
"Someone good at parallel parking."

00:29:42.605 --> 00:29:46.146
"Someone who eats three bowls of rice."
"Someone who bowls over 200."

00:29:46.230 --> 00:29:49.480
Well, I thought I'd write down
my preferences in detail.

00:29:49.563 --> 00:29:50.521
It's too detailed.

00:29:50.605 --> 00:29:54.271
What does "Dogs, cats, and birds are okay,
but reptiles are not" mean?

00:29:54.355 --> 00:29:57.563
Well, I want someone
who likes dogs, cats, and birds as pets

00:29:57.646 --> 00:29:59.146
but not reptiles.

00:30:00.230 --> 00:30:03.688
Finding someone that specific
is like looking for a cryptid.

00:30:04.355 --> 00:30:05.980
What? What's a cryptid?

00:30:06.063 --> 00:30:08.563
Huh? Doesn't Attorney Kujo fit
the description?

00:30:08.646 --> 00:30:11.313
You have Black Thunder.
You're good at bowling, right?

00:30:11.396 --> 00:30:13.480
My best score is 292.

00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:16.146
What do you think?

00:30:16.230 --> 00:30:18.813
No way! I'd never like
a crooked lawyer like him.

00:30:18.896 --> 00:30:20.230
Because he's crooked?

00:30:20.313 --> 00:30:21.730
No, that's not it.

00:30:21.813 --> 00:30:22.813
Then,

00:30:23.563 --> 00:30:24.521
Attorney Karasuma?

00:30:26.771 --> 00:30:30.605
I hate an accomplice
of a crooked lawyer even more.

00:30:34.896 --> 00:30:37.605
Let's go to another place,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:30:37.688 --> 00:30:39.646
Remember? You don't like me.

00:30:40.188 --> 00:30:43.271
Are you still sulking?
You're coming, right?

00:30:43.355 --> 00:30:47.355
You're not like that heartless Kujo
who went home early, right?

00:30:48.855 --> 00:30:50.355
Attorney.

00:30:53.646 --> 00:30:54.855
You know him?

00:30:54.938 --> 00:30:55.771
Huh?

00:30:56.271 --> 00:30:57.105
Well--

00:30:57.188 --> 00:31:02.105
Thank you for the settlement.
Chairman Koyama was grateful too.

00:31:02.188 --> 00:31:05.605
But how did you persuade that AV actress?

00:31:06.188 --> 00:31:07.146
AV?

00:31:07.646 --> 00:31:10.896
Well, it was Attorney Kujo
who did the work.

00:31:10.980 --> 00:31:12.188
But

00:31:12.730 --> 00:31:15.896
you helped him too, right?

00:31:18.730 --> 00:31:22.813
I'll buy you a fancy ice cream
as a thank you next time.

00:31:30.605 --> 00:31:32.521
I knew you were an accomplice to evil.

00:31:32.605 --> 00:31:33.688
No, I'm not.

00:31:34.438 --> 00:31:38.021
No matter how much you deny it,
if you're with him, that's how it looks.

00:31:40.521 --> 00:31:41.730
I'm sober now.

00:31:42.855 --> 00:31:43.938
I'm going home.

00:31:53.646 --> 00:31:56.313
I'm really worried about you, you know?

00:31:58.396 --> 00:32:01.396
Both Attorney Kujo and you.

00:32:12.563 --> 00:32:13.396
Here you go.

00:32:17.063 --> 00:32:21.063
I used to walk my dog every morning
around this time…

00:32:23.438 --> 00:32:27.021
because the summer asphalt
is like a cigarette burn on a dog's paws.

00:32:29.521 --> 00:32:31.688
When Rice Cake's legs became weak,

00:32:32.563 --> 00:32:36.230
I would use a dogcart,
and we'd take shorter walks.

00:32:38.438 --> 00:32:39.771
Rice Cake.

00:32:41.605 --> 00:32:45.105
My dog looked so happy
when the breeze blew across its cheeks.

00:32:46.105 --> 00:32:47.355
That face…

00:32:48.188 --> 00:32:51.730
As I walked, I wondered how many
more times I'd get to see that face.

00:32:56.438 --> 00:32:57.730
When I was a kid,

00:32:58.480 --> 00:33:00.521
I used to fight and get hit.

00:33:01.271 --> 00:33:04.230
After everything that happened,
my heart grew cold and numb.

00:33:09.396 --> 00:33:11.855
Dogs can understand
what's going on in your heart.

00:33:12.813 --> 00:33:16.438
My dog would comfort me and lick my face.

00:33:18.105 --> 00:33:21.646
When I rubbed my nose against
Rice Cake's body and took a deep breath,

00:33:22.146 --> 00:33:25.563
I smelled a fragrant scent
I couldn't describe that calmed me.

00:33:28.563 --> 00:33:30.021
After my mom died,

00:33:30.980 --> 00:33:34.146
Rice Cake was the only one
I could open my heart to.

00:33:35.521 --> 00:33:37.355
Did Rice Cake die of old age?

00:33:43.021 --> 00:33:45.146
I killed my dog on Kyogoku's orders.

00:33:47.021 --> 00:33:50.855
I should've killed him myself,
right then and there.

00:33:54.230 --> 00:33:55.938
But now's not the time.

00:33:57.896 --> 00:34:00.063
